#How much does sequencing cost?

cost <- read.csv(file = file.path(data.dir,"raw_data/Sequencing_Costs_Table_July_2017.csv"), header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
cost <- cost[,1:4]
cost$Date <- as.Date(cost$Date)
head(cost)
one <- as.numeric(as.Date("2001-01-01"))
seventeen <- as.numeric(as.Date("2018-01-01"))
x.at <- seq(one, seventeen, 365)
x.lab <- 2001:2018
x.at
 [1] 11323 11688 12053 12418 12783 13148 13513 13878 14243 14608 14973 15338 15703 16068 16433 16798 17163 17528
x.lab
 [1] 2001 2002 2003 2004 2005 2006 2007 2008 2009 2010 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015 2016 2017 2018
options(scipen = 10000000)
y.lab <- seq(0,100,20)
y.at <- y.lab * 10^6
plot(x = cost$Date, y = cost$Cost.per.Genome/10^6, ylab = "Cost per genome (million $)", xlab = "", col = pal[1], pch = 19, xaxt = "n", las = 1)
axis(side = 1, at = x.at, labels = x.lab, las = 2)
mtext(text = "Year", side = 1, line = 3.5)

plot(x = cost$Date, y = cost$Cost.per.Genome/10^6, ylab = "Cost per genome (million $)", xlim = c(x.at[7],x.at[18]), ylim = c(0,10), xlab = "", col = pal[1], pch = 19, xaxt = "n", las = 1)
axis(side = 1, at = x.at, labels = x.lab, las = 2)
mtext(text = "Year", side = 1, line = 3.5)

#How many samples are in GEO?

geo <- read.csv(file = file.path(data.dir,"raw_data/20190523_GEOcontent.csv"), header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
geo[,1:5] <- apply(X = geo[,1:5], MARGIN = 2, FUN = function(X){
  this.col <- X
  this.col <- gsub(pattern = ",", replacement = "", x = X)
  this.col <- as.numeric(this.col)
  this.col <- rev(this.col)
})
head(geo)
years <- unique(geo$Year)
years
 [1] 2000 2001 2002 2003 2004 2005 2006 2007 2008 2009 2010 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015 2016 2017 2018 2019
n.samples <- sapply(X = years,FUN = function(X){
  this.year <- X
  this.n <- geo$Samples[which(geo$Year==this.year)]
  max(this.n)
})
n.samples
 [1]      10     670    2645   10386   28258   63642  109420  187389  272290  383416  509542  673147  851936 1054764
[15] 1306820 1572306 1920368 2314227 2818554 3045210
y.labels <- seq(0,3,0.5)
y.at <- y.labels * 10^6
par(mar = c(5,5,2,2))
barplot(height = n.samples, axes = FALSE, pch = 19, xlab = "", ylab = "", col = pal[2], main = "Number of samples in GEO", names.arg = years, las = 2, border = NA)
axis(side = 1, at = years, labels = years, las = 2) 
axis(side = 2, at = y.at, labels = y.labels, las = 1)
mtext(text = "Year", side = 1, line = 4)
mtext(text = "# Samples (million)", side = 2, line = 3)
